The paper discusses the organization of databases for online analytical processing (OLAP) applications, which is a topic related to database management systems (DBMS) and data structures (DS). Therefore, cs.DB and cs.DS are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also discusses the efficiency of handling sparse matrices, which is a topic related to information retrieval (IR) and artificial intelligence (AI). Finally, the paper presents experimental results on the speed of the two different database organizations, which is a topic related to machine learning (LG).
